 political modernism to psychoanalysis and theories of sexual difference. In a new introduction written especially for this edition, Rodowick considers the continuing legacy of this theoretical tradition in relation to the emergence of cultural studies approaches to film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFilm criticismxPolitical aspects. 0aFilm criticism. 0aMotion picturesxPolitical aspects. 0aMotion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a1970s film theory.  a20th century film.  a20th century filmmakers.  a20th century politics.  acinema history.  aeuropean films.  aeuropean history.  afeminism.  afilm and feminism.  afilm and politics.  afilm and television.  afilm critics.  afilm history.  afilm symbolism.  afilm theory.  afrench films.  agender and film.  agender studies.  ahistory of filmmaking.  ahistory of france.  ajean-luc godard.  alaura mulvey.  amarxism.  amovie theory.  apeter gidal.  apeter wollen.  apostwar entertainment.  apsychoanalysis.  asemiotics.  astructuralism.  awomens studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008771240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520915169?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520915169423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520915169/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY